sentences: John Munson (born December 13, 1966) is an American musician who is best known as the bass player for Semisonic.
He was also a member of Trip Shakespeare during the late 1980s and early 1990s.

Matt Wilson, lead vocalist of Trip Shakespeare, recalled how Munson joined that band in 1985:
John is somebody that I'd played with in a band a few years earlier, so we already knew each other.

Currently Munson is working on several different projects, including working with former Trip Shakespeare mate Matt Wilson on new songs as The Flops and later The Twilight Hours, and also on the New Standards, a band that plays covers of a wide variety of music in a jazz format.
